The readme shows usage of upload_stream like this:
```javascript
cloudinary.uploader.upload_stream(
  { agent: myAgent },
  function(error, result) { console.log(result); }
);
```

But from my testing of v1.14.0, the callback needs to be before the options.
And in the current source in [libuploader.js](https://github.com/cloudinary/cloudinary_npm/blob/master/lib/uploader.js) I see this:
```javascript
exports.upload_stream = function upload_stream(callback, options = {}) {
  return exports.upload(null, callback, extend({
    stream: true
  }, options));
};
```

`upload` seems to suffer from the same mismatch. I'd make a pull request to change the readme, but perhaps the code should be updated to allow for an option options object before the callback?

